Package software.leonov.common.collect

Class MoreLists

  • java.lang.Object
    • software.leonov.common.collect.MoreLists
  • public class MoreLists
extends Object
    More static utility methods which operate on or return Lists.

    Note: Methods in this class accept java.util.function.Predicates which are interchangeable with their their Guava counterparts com.google.common.base.Predicates, see com.google.common.base.Predicate for more information.

    Author:
    Zhenya Leonov
    See Also:
    Maps, MoreMaps, Collections, Collections2, Lists, MoreLists, Sets, Iterables, Iterators, Iteration, Queues, MoreQueues, Arrays, ObjectArrays, MoreArrays

      • indexOf

        public static <E> int indexOf​(List<E> list,
                              Predicate<? super E> predicate,
                              int fromIndex)
        Returns the index of the first occurrence in the specified list of an element which satisfies the given predicate, starting the search at fromIndex, or -1 if there is no such element.

        Note: If the specified list allows null elements the given predicate must be able to handle null inputs to avoid a NullPointerException.

        Type Parameters:
        E - the element type
        Parameters:
        list - the specified list
        predicate - the given predicate
        fromIndex - the index to start the search from (inclusive)
        Returns:
        the index of the first occurrence in the specified list of an element which satisfies the given predicate, starting the search at fromIndex, or -1 if there is no such element
        See Also:
        Iterables#indexOf(Iterable, Predicate)
